# mascot.md — Bramble (Ferndle) — FIXTURE EXAMPLE

<!-- This is the worked example of the mascot recipe schema (Mascot Lane, D3).
     "Ferndle" and "Bramble" are a fictional, neutral fixture brand invented for
     this repo's tests — not a real product. Copy this shape, not this content. -->

## Recipe

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| generator | `z-image-turbo` — HF Space `mcp-tools/Z-Image-Turbo` (as of 2026-07-07) |
| seed | `77` |
| resolution | `1024×1024` |

**LOCK** (the character — one paragraph, never edited after acceptance):

> cute chibi hedgehog mascot with large round friendly eyes and a gentle open
> smile, short rounded quills, warm tan #D9A066 fur, deep brown #5B3A29 rounded
> quills and markings, bright golden amber #F2C14E eyes, wearing a golden amber
> #F2C14E neckerchief bandana, tiny moss green #4A7C59 hiking backpack, small
> brown hiking boots, flat sticker illustration style, bold clean outlines, flat
> colors, white sticker border, plain pale cream #F5EDDF background, full body,
> standing front-facing, wholesome children's book character

**POSE pattern:** a new pose appends exactly one line to the locked prompt —
`POSE: <one line>` — and changes nothing else. Examples used for this fixture:

- `POSE: waving hello with one paw raised`
- `POSE: mid-hike, holding a tiny wooden walking stick`
- `POSE: sitting, writing in a tiny open journal with a stub pencil`
- `POSE: arms raised in a summit celebration`

**DERIVE lanes** (utilities, not heroes):

- cutout → transparent PNG (`python3 <skill-dir>/scripts/verify.py cutout <brand-root>/mascot/master.png <brand-root>/mascot/master-transparent.png`; `<skill-dir>` = this skill's loaded directory, `<brand-root>` = the user-project brand root)
- vtracer → SVG (scale/print convenience only)
- quantize → pixel (quick retro moments; a *hero* pixel mascot is a separate
  native `pixel-art` generation with its own locked recipe)

**Known limits:** cross-pose generative drift — quill count, boot shape, and
bandana knot wander between poses. The canon master is authoritative; regenerate
an off-model pose rather than accepting it. Seed reproducibility is bound to the
generator version recorded above — a Space update may change the render for the
same seed.

**standing front-facing IS CANON.**

## Palette anchors (steering, not spec)

| Role | Hex | Where it lives |
|---|---|---|
| ground | `#D9A066` | fur |
| brand-dark | `#5B3A29` | quills, markings |
| accent | `#4A7C59` | backpack |
| spark | `#F2C14E` | eyes, neckerchief |
| ground-tint | `#F5EDDF` | sticker background |

Acceptance is the palette-anchor gate (`python3 <skill-dir>/scripts/verify.py anchors <brand-root>/mascot/master.png ...` — every
declared anchor ≥ 0.5% pixel share at tol 60), never exact hex reproduction.
